content:
@everyone from my journal five years ago yesterday:

"I’ve been working with Hendrick and Iggy getting the discord server up, and just sent out a bunch of invites. It’s cool to see the beginnings of a community happen. I’m getting all these creative ideas just thinking about what’s possible. It’s also a testament to just DOING things. Even if there isn’t a solid goal in mind. When you do things, you learn things."

Big love to @hendrick and @1ggy who were the first ones involved to help make this place happen. I'm so proud of all of you for helping keep this community thriving. You all put kindness and curiosity and patience first, and THAT is what makes this place special. An island in the sea of fuckery that is the internet. I appreciate you all, my friends!

@everyone we hit 2000 people on the discord! I appreciate all of you so much for helping to create such a beautiful and rich community. 

I would love it if people want to share a small thought or anecdote about what they've gotten from this space. I know I've learned a huge amount from reading other people discuss and debate things about audio. But I've also learned a ton about nurturing and creating parameters for an online community that continues to be useful and supportive, despite growing to more than two thousand people 😧. 

This place is so special! Thank you all!

@everyone I also want to give a big special thank you and shoutout to the moderators: 

@slow.hand , who in addition to the incredible show notes for every conversation, puts more thought and time into the workings of this discord and the live streams than anyone.

@hendrick & @1ggy, who were instrumental in the creation of this space, and continue to be huge contributors behind the scenes. 

@Nomograph Mastering, our own Master Splinter/ Master Oogway, who has contributed more deep, consistent, thoughtful knowledge than anyone.

@cian riordan & @BatMeckley, our Mick and Keith, our Jay Z and Beyoncé, our Caligula and his horse. Two incredible record makers (with one Grammy between them!) who consistently make us laugh and think.

@Rollmottle & @NoahNeedleman, who were such beautiful and consistent parts of the community that they earned the responsibility of becoming our most recent moderators. 

And @Davi Juno, who doesn't post much here, but has done all the editing and formatting for the YouTube versions of the Instagram streams, as well as all the clips.

All of these people are hugely responsible for this space!

@everyone tik tok/ reels help needed for LWMR. 

I'm still looking for someone to help create and manage tik tok/ reels content for the discussions. We have SO much content that would be perfect to chop up into 60 second videos. This would help get the info out to a much larger audience. But I don't have the time to do it myself and I haven't found anyone great who I can collaborate on it with.

Can anyone in the community help? or help make a connection?
